@startuml Unified_Parkinson_Prediction_Flow
title Parkinson's Disease Prediction System - Unified Flow Diagram\n(User Journey + Algorithm Internal Architecture)

skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam defaultFontColor black
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam ArrowColor black
skinparam ActivityBackgroundColor white
skinparam ActivityBorderColor black
skinparam PartitionBorderColor black
skinparam PartitionBackgroundColor #F8F9FA
skinparam NoteFontSize 9

||#E3F2FD|**USER INTERACTION LAYER**|
start

:User opens Parkinson's Detection System;

:User logs in or registers;
note right
  Authentication via JWT
  User session management
  Access control
end note

:User navigates to prediction interface;

:User selects input modality;
note right
  Options:
  • Speech (audio file)
  • Handwriting (image)
  • Gait (video)
  • Combined video
  • Manual feature input
end note

||#FFF3E0|**DATA INPUT & VALIDATION LAYER**|

if (Input type?) then (Audio File)
  :POST /api/upload/audio;
  :Validate audio file (format, size, duration);
  if (Valid?) then (yes)
    :Save temporary audio file;
  else (no)
    :Return error "Invalid audio file";
    stop
  endif
elseif (Image File)
  :POST /api/upload/handwriting;
  :Validate image file (format, size, quality);
  if (Valid?) then (yes)
    :Save temporary image file;
  else (no)
    :Return error "Invalid image file";
    stop
  endif
elseif (Video File)
  :POST /api/upload/gait;
  :Validate video file (format, size, duration);
  if (Valid?) then (yes)
    :Save temporary video file;
  else (no)
    :Return error "Invalid video file";
    stop
  endif
elseif (Combined Video)
  :POST /api/process_combined_video;
  :Validate combined video + extraction flags;
  if (Valid?) then (yes)
    :Save temporary video file;
  else (no)
    :Return error "Invalid combined video";
    stop
  endif
else (Manual Features)
  :User inputs feature values directly;
  :Validate feature counts and ranges;
endif

||#E8F5E8|**FEATURE EXTRACTION LAYER**|

if (Processing type?) then (Audio Processing)
  :Load audio using soundfile/librosa;
  :Apply noise reduction and normalization;
  :Extract using Parselmouth (Praat);
  fork
    :Fundamental Frequency Features;
    :F0, Fhi, Flo;
  fork again
    :Voice Quality Features;
    :Jitter (%, Abs, RAP, PPQ, DDP);
    :Shimmer (%, dB, APQ3, APQ5, APQ, DDA);
    :NHR, HNR;
  fork again
    :Nonlinear Dynamics Features;
    :RPDE, DFA, spread1, spread2, D2, PPE;
  end fork
  :Combine into 22 speech features;
  
elseif (Image Processing)
  :Load image using OpenCV/PIL;
  :Convert to grayscale and binarize;
  :Detect strokes and contours;
  fork
    :Pressure & Force Features;
    :mean_pressure, std_pressure;
  fork again
    :Kinematic Features;
    :mean_velocity, std_velocity, mean_acceleration;
  fork again
    :Temporal & Motor Features;
    :pen_up_time, writing_tempo, stroke_length;
    :tremor_frequency, fluency_score;
  end fork
  :Combine into 10 handwriting features;
  
elseif (Video Processing)
  :Load video using OpenCV;
  :Extract frames and convert to grayscale;
  :Compute frame differences for motion;
  :Detect step peaks and intervals;
  fork
    :Temporal Features;
    :stride_interval, stride_interval_std;
    :swing_time, stance_time, double_support;
  fork again
    :Spatial & Rhythm Features;
    :step_length, gait_speed, cadence;
    :stride_regularity, gait_asymmetry;
  end fork
  :Combine into 10 gait features;
  
elseif (Combined Video)
  fork
    :Extract audio track → WAV;
    :Process audio → 22 speech features;
  fork again
    :Extract middle frame → Image;
    :Process image → 10 handwriting features;
  fork again
    :Analyze full video → Motion;
    :Process motion → 10 gait features;
  end fork
  :Combine all extracted features;
  
else (Manual Input)
  :Use provided feature values;
  :Validate feature counts (22/10/10);
endif

:Delete temporary files;
:Return extracted features to client;

note right
  **Feature Extraction Results:**
  • Speech: 22 numerical features
  • Handwriting: 10 numerical features  
  • Gait: 10 numerical features
  • All features represent patterns that
    can indicate Parkinson's symptoms
end note

||#F3E5F5|**MODEL PROCESSING LAYER**|

:Client calls POST /api/predict with features;
:Validate at least one modality provided;
:Build input vectors for model;

if (All three modalities?) then (yes)
  :Use all three real feature vectors;
  :speech_features [22], handwriting_features [10], gait_features [10];
else (missing modalities)
  :Zero-fill missing modalities;
  :Missing speech → [0,0,0...] (22 zeros);
  :Missing handwriting → [0,0,0...] (10 zeros);
  :Missing gait → [0,0,0...] (10 zeros);
endif

:Apply feature scaling using saved scalers;
:speech_scaled, handwriting_scaled, gait_scaled;

note right
  **Model Input Preparation:**
  • Always 3 vectors: [22], [10], [10]
  • Real data or zero-filled
  • Scaled using training statistics
  • Consistent input format for model
end note

||#E1F5FE|**SE-RESNET ENCODER LAYER**|

:Pass scaled vectors to SE-ResNet 1D CNN encoders;

fork
  :**Speech Encoder**;
  :Input: speech_scaled [1, 22];
  :**Stem**: Conv1d(1→32) + BatchNorm + ReLU;
  :Transform input into 32 feature maps;
  
  :**Block 1**: Residual SE Block;
  :Conv1d + BN + ReLU + Conv1d + BN;
  :SE Module: GlobalAvgPool → FC(32→8) → ReLU → FC(8→32) → Sigmoid;
  :Channel attention weighting;
  :Add skip connection + ReLU;
  
  :**Block 2**: Residual SE Block (32→64);
  :Conv1d(32→64) + BN + ReLU + Conv1d + BN;
  :SE Module: GlobalAvgPool → FC(64→16) → ReLU → FC(16→64) → Sigmoid;
  :Channel attention weighting;
  :Add skip connection + ReLU;
  
  :**Pool & Linear**: AdaptiveAvgPool1d(1) → Linear(64→64);
  :Output: **speech_embedding [64]**;

fork again
  :**Handwriting Encoder**;
  :Input: handwriting_scaled [1, 10];
  :**Stem**: Conv1d(1→32) + BatchNorm + ReLU;
  :**Block 1**: Residual SE Block (32→32);
  :**Block 2**: Residual SE Block (32→64);
  :**Pool & Linear**: AdaptiveAvgPool1d(1) → Linear(64→64);
  :Output: **handwriting_embedding [64]**;

fork again
  :**Gait Encoder**;
  :Input: gait_scaled [1, 10];
  :**Stem**: Conv1d(1→32) + BatchNorm + ReLU;
  :**Block 1**: Residual SE Block (32→32);
  :**Block 2**: Residual SE Block (32→64);
  :**Pool & Linear**: AdaptiveAvgPool1d(1) → Linear(64→64);
  :Output: **gait_embedding [64]**;
end fork

:Collect three 64-dimensional embeddings;
:Stack embeddings → [3, 64] tensor;

note right
  **SE-ResNet Encoder Results:**
  • 3 parallel encoders (same architecture)
  • Each processes one modality independently
  • Stem: Initial pattern detection
  • Blocks: Deep feature learning with skip connections
  • SE: Channel attention for important patterns
  • Output: 3 × 64D embeddings (pattern summaries)
end note

||#FFF8E1|**ATTENTION FUSION LAYER**|

:Compute attention scores for each embedding;

fork
  :speech_embedding [64] → Linear(64→32) → Tanh → Linear(32→1);
  :Output: speech_score;
fork again
  :handwriting_embedding [64] → Linear(64→32) → Tanh → Linear(32→1);
  :Output: handwriting_score;
fork again
  :gait_embedding [64] → Linear(64→32) → Tanh → Linear(32→1);
  :Output: gait_score;
end fork

:Apply Softmax to scores;
:attention_weights = Softmax([speech_score, handwriting_score, gait_score]);

:Compute weighted fusion;
:fused_embedding = Σ(attention_weights[i] × embeddings[i]);
:Result: **fused_embedding [64]** + **attention_weights [3]**;

note right
  **Attention Fusion Process:**
  • Score each modality's importance
  • Convert scores to probabilities (sum=1.0)
  • Weighted combination of embeddings
  • Example weights: [0.55, 0.15, 0.30]
  • Higher weight = more trusted modality
  • Handles missing data automatically
end note

||#E8F8E8|**DENSE CLASSIFICATION LAYER**|

:Input: fused_embedding [64];

:**Layer 1**: Linear(64→32) + ReLU + Dropout(0.3);
:Compress and add non-linearity;
:Output: intermediate_features [32];

:**Layer 2**: Linear(32→1);
:Final classification layer;
:Output: **logit** (raw prediction score);

:Apply Sigmoid to convert logit to probability;
:probability = 1 / (1 + exp(-logit));

:Make binary decision using threshold;
if (probability >= 0.5?) then (yes)
  :prediction = "Parkinson's";
else (no)
  :prediction = "Healthy";
endif

:confidence = probability;

note right
  **Classification Process:**
  • Dense layers for final decision
  • Dropout prevents overfitting
  • Sigmoid converts to probability [0,1]
  • Threshold 0.5 for binary classification
  • Confidence = raw probability value
end note

||#F0E8FF|**OUTPUT & RESPONSE LAYER**|

:Prepare comprehensive response;

:Build JSON response with:;
note right
  {
    "prediction": "Parkinson's" | "Healthy",
    "confidence": 0.85,
    "probability": 0.85,
    "attention_weights": {
      "speech": 0.55,
      "handwriting": 0.15,
      "gait": 0.30
    },
    "features": {
      "speech_features": [22 values],
      "handwriting_features": [10 values],
      "gait_features": [10 values]
    },
    "model_info": {
      "model_type": "SE-ResNet + Attention",
      "version": "1.0"
    }
  }
end note

:Save prediction to database (if authenticated);
:Return 200 OK with prediction results;

||#E3F2FD|**USER INTERFACE LAYER**|

:Display results to user;

:Show prediction with confidence;
:Visualize attention weights (which tests were most important);
:Display feature values used;
:Provide explanation of results;

note right
  **User-Friendly Output:**
  • Clear Parkinson's/Healthy result
  • Confidence percentage (0-100%)
  • Which tests contributed most
  • Visual charts and explanations
  • Option to save or share results
end note

:User can perform another prediction or logout;

stop

note bottom
  **System Capabilities Summary:**
  ✓ Handles 1, 2, or 3 modalities flexibly
  ✓ Real-time feature extraction from raw files
  ✓ Advanced AI with attention mechanism
  ✓ Explainable results with confidence metrics
  ✓ Secure, scalable web-based deployment
  ✓ Clinical-grade accuracy and reliability
end note

@enduml